channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Battleground state rancher ‘outraged’ by Biden stopping wall construction as migrants pour into US
item.description: Arizona rancher Jim Chilton says he has had more than 3,500 migrants come across the border since the Biden administration took office and stopped wall construction.

item.title: Thousands of Capitol Hill staffers' info spilled across dark web, security firm says
item.description: Personal information for some 3,191 congressional staffers has been leaked across the dark web, according to new research from internet security firm Proton being released Tuesday.

item.title: Courts Are Letting Social-Media Platforms Get Away with Manipulating Children
item.description: A Utah judge was wrong to strike down the state’s attempt to protect kids from social media’s harms.

item.title: Vulnerable Democrat Montana Senator Can’t Hide From Harris’ Long Left Shadow
item.description: Jon Tester has refused to endorse the Vice President, but the three-term senator has long stood by the far-left presidential candidate.

item.title: New poll indicates whether Harris or Trump is making gains with younger voters
item.description: A new poll indicates surging support among America's youngest voters for Vice President Kamala Harris in her 2024 showdown against former President Trump.

item.title: Supreme Court keeps federal horse racing law in effect, for now
item.description: The Supreme Court on Monday put on hold -- for now -- a lower court ruling that had said a federal law regulating the safety of horse racing was unconstitutional.

item.title: Israel’s Righteous War on Hezbollah
item.description: The Jewish state is under no obligation to tolerate the intolerable.

item.title: Corporate Media’s Kamala Coverup Is Next-Level Election Interference
item.description: It's the Hunter Biden laptop scandal all over again as the usual accomplice media suspects protect Harris from herself.

item.title: Absentee voting kicks off in Missouri, North Carolina
item.description: Missouri and North Carolina began early voting on Tuesday, joining roughly 20 other states as the 2024 election kicks off.

item.title: Senators urge Supreme Court to bolster First Step Act's sentence reduction
item.description: A bipartisan group of senators asked the Supreme Court on Monday to allow defendants that have had their original sentences vacated to be resentenced under new criminal justice reforms passed in 2018.

item.title: Abortion Advocates Are Lying about the Tragic Deaths in Georgia
item.description: The media focus on two women who died as a result of chemically induced abortions outright ignores the law, the facts, and the situation in other nations.

item.title: Ukraine’s Zelensky Used U.S. Military Assets To Campaign For Harris in Pennsylvania
item.description: Zelensky's visit with Harris surrogates in Pennsylvania comes one day after The New Yorker published an interview in which he criticized Trump and Vance.

item.title: Fani Willis crisscrosses country fundraising with Democrat allies in DC, LA
item.description: Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis traveled to Washington, D.C., Los Angeles and Texas to fundraise with Democratic allies for her re-election campaign.

item.title: Oregon election officials remove people who didn't provide proof of citizenship from voter rolls
item.description: Oregon elections officials said Monday they had struck over 1,200 people from the state's voter rolls after determining they did not provide proof of U.S. citizenship when they were registered to vote.

item.title: The No. 1 conservative virtue, &c.
item.description: On prudence, Poland, Mark Robinson, George W. Bush, the Big O, pumpkin spice, Milwaukee, and more.

item.title: Lawsuit: Nevada Clerks Are Failing To Process Challenges To Voter Rolls
item.description: The lawsuit comes after Secretary of State Cisco Agular instructed local officials to reject voter roll challenges that did not comply with his office's interpretation of the law.

item.title: Piling on: A tsunami of anti-Trump pieces offer a stark contrast with Kamala’s upbeat coverage
item.description: Presidential candidates Donald Trump and Kamala Harris are running in the same election cycle, however, the coverage of each White House hopeful starkly contrasts.

item.title: Trump threatens to slap 200% tariff on John Deere goods if it moves some production to Mexico
item.description: Former President Donald Trump warned Monday that if John Deere follows through with moving some of its production to Mexico, he will slap those imports into the United States with a 200% tariff.

item.title: Americans Are Paying for Out-of-Control Federal Spending
item.description: The burgeoning deficit is not a revenue problem but a spending problem.

item.title: FTC Commissioner Warns New Report Could Be Used By Big Tech To Justify Censorship
item.description: Melissa Holyoak is concerned that the FTC’s repeated calls for 'more stringent testing and monitoring standards' could put Americans’ First Amendment rights at further risk of infringement.
